name: Source/API.js
SketchAPIWithCapturedContext
description:
Return a function that captures the context.
When called, this function will initialise the API
and return an Application object that provides access
to all API functions.

We do it like this to defer having to perform a lot
of setup until context.api() is actually called -- thus
scripts which don't call it at all suffer minimal overhead.

name: Source/Application.js
Application
description:
Gives you access to Sketch, and provides access to:
- the document model and the layer tree
- metadata abound sketch itself
- utilities for interacting with the user
- access to the running plugin, it's resources and settings

name: constructor
description:
Construct a new Application object.
An instance of this class will be passed back to you when you
initialise the API, so you generally shouldn't need to make new ones.

params.name: context
params.description: The context dictionary passed to the script when it was invoked.

return.description: A new Application object.

name: _metadata
description: Metadata about this version of Sketch.

name: factory
description:
This is a slightly clumsy way to pass related classes into Layer
without setting up a circular dependency between classes (eg Layer imports Artboard which imports Layer...)
there has to be a better way to do this...

name: api_version
description: The version of this API.

return.description: A version string.

name: context
description:
The context that the API was created in.
This is the traditional context argument that is
passed to all plugin scripts when they are run.

In general you should use the API to access Sketch
rather than interacting with the context directly.

return.description: A context dictionary.

name: version
description: The version of Sketch that is running.

return.description: The version as a string, eg "3.6".

name: build
description: The exact build of Sketch that is running.

return.description: The build number as a string, eg "15352".

name: full_version
description: Returns the full version of Sketch that is running

return.description: Version and build number as a string, eg "3.6 (15352)".

name: settingForKey
description: Return the value of a global setting for a given key.

params.name: key
params.description: The setting to look up.

return.description:
The setting value.

This is equivalent to reading a setting for the currently
running version of Sketch using the `defaults` command line tool,
eg: defaults read com.bohemiancoding.sketch3 <key>

name: setSettingForKey
description: Set the value of a global setting for a given key.

params.name: key
params.description: The setting to set.

params.name: value
params.description:
The value to set it to.

This is equivalent to writing a setting for the currently
running version of Sketch using the `defaults` command line tool,
eg: defaults write com.bohemiancoding.sketch3 <key> <value>

name: resourceNamed
description:
Return a file URL pointing to a named resource in the plugin's Resources/
folder.

params.name: name
params.description: The resource file name, including any file extension.

return.description: The resource location, in the form "file://path/to/resource".

name: getStringFromUser
description:
Shows a simple input sheet which displays a message, and asks for a single string
input.

params.name: msg
params.description: The prompt message to show.

params.name: initial
params.description: The initial value of the input string.

return.description: The string that the user input.

name: getSelectionFromUser
description:
Shows an input sheet which displays a popup with a series of options,
from which the user is asked to choose.

params.name: msg
params.description: The prompt message to show.

params.name: items
params.description: A list of option items.

params.name: selectedItemIndex
params.description: The index of the item to select initially.

return.description:
An array with two items: [responseCode, selection].

The result consists of a response code and a selection. The code will be
one of NSAlertFirstButtonReturn or NSAlertSecondButtonReturn.
The selection will be the integer index of the selected item.

name: log
description: Output a message to the log console.

params.name: message
params.description: The message to output.

name: assert
description:
Assert that a given condition is true.
If the condition is false, throws an exception.

params.name: condition
params.description: An expression that is expected to evaluate to true if everything is ok.

name: selectedDocument
description:
The selected document.

If the user invoked the script explicitly (for example by selecting a menu item),
this will be the document that they were working in at the time - ie the frontmost one.
If the script was invoked as an action handler, this will be the document that the action
occurred in.

return.description: A Document object.

name: newDocument
description: Create a new document and bring it to the front.

return.description: The new document.

name: message
description:
Show a small, temporary, message to the user.
The message appears at the bottom of the selected document,
and is visible for a short period of time. It should consist of a single
line of text.

params.name: message
params.description: The message to show.

name: alert
description: Show an alert with a custom title and message.

params.name: title
params.description: The title of the alert.

params.name: message
params.description:
The text of the message.

The alert is modal, so it will stay around until the user dismisses it
by pressing the OK button.

name: rectangle
description: Return a new Rectangle object for a given x,y, width and height.

params.name: x
params.description: The x coordinate of the top-left corner of the rectangle.

params.name: y
params.description: The y coordinate of the top-left corner of the rectangle.

params.name: width
params.description: The width of the rectangle.

params.name: height
params.description: The height of the rectangle.

return.description: The new Rectangle object.

name: Source/Document.js

name: constructor
description: Make a new document object.

params.name: document
params.description: The underlying MSDocument object.

params.name: application
params.description:
The application object.

Note that constructing one of these doesn't actually create
a Sketch document. Instead you pass in the underlying MSDocument
that this object represents.

If you do want to create a new document, you can do so with Application#newDocument.

name: _application
description: The application that this document belongs to.

name: selectedPage

return.description: A page object representing the page that the user is currently viewing.

name: layerNamed

The new frame should be given in coordinates that are local to the parent of the layer.

Duplicate this layer.
A new identical layer will be inserted into the parent of this layer.

return.description: A new layer identical to this one.

Is this a page?

Is this an group?

name: _addWrappedLayerWithProperties
description:
Add a new wrapped layer object to represent a Sketch layer.
Apply any supplied properties to the wrapper (which will apply
them in turn to the wrapped layer).

params.name: newLayer
params.description: The underlying Sketch layer object.

params.name: properties
params.description: The properties to apply.

params.name: wrapper
params.description: The name of wrapper class to use.

return.description: The wrapped layer object.

name: _frameForLayerWithProperties
description:
Extract the frame to use for a layer from some properties.
If the frame wasn't supplied in the properties, we return a default value instead.

params.name: properties
params.description: The properties to use when looking for a frame value.

return.description: The frame rectangle to use.

name: newShape
description:
Returns a newly created shape, which has been added to this layer,
and sets it up using the supplied properties.

params.name: properties
params.description: {dictionary} Properties to apply to the shape.

return.description: the new shape.

name: newText
description:
Returns a newly created text layer, which has been added to this layer,
and sets it up using the supplied properties.

params.name: properties
params.description: Properties to apply to the text layer.

return.description: the new text layer.

name: newGroup
description:
Returns a newly created group, which has been added to this layer,
and sets it up using the supplied properties.

params.name: properties
params.description: Properties to apply to the group.

name: newImage
description:
Returns a newly created image layer, which has been added to this layer,

params.name: properties
params.description: Properties to apply to the layer.

return.description: the new image layer.

name: remove
description: Remove this layer from its parent.

name: select
description:
Select the layer.
This will clear the previous selection. Use addToSelection() if you wish
to preserve the existing selection.

name: deselect
description:
Deselect this layer.
Any other layers that were previously selected will remain selected.

name: addToSelection
description:
Add this layer to the selected layers.
Any other layers that were previously selected will remain selected.

name: iterate
description:
Perform a function for every sub-layer inside this one.
The function will be passed a single argument each time it is
invoked - which will be an object representing the sub-layer.

params.name: block
params.description: {function} The function to execute for each layer.
